answer: I see. Well, in that case inspect it and see what's wrong. When you need help, provide a working example and I'll have a look. Happy coding!

One way would be to have two indices (`get` and `put`) move forward through the array.  If they're not equal, then you copy `str[get]` to `str[put]`.  If `str[get]` is a space, then you increment `get` (but don't copy).  That way, everything that's not a space will get squashed up towards the front of the array.
